## DNS Tunnel (iodine)

iodine is a DNS request only tunnel, it's purpose is to provide a direct IP path through environments that only allow real DNS traffic. It provides no encryption.



### DNS delegation required for iodine

For this to work, you need a nameserver you can query.

Add two records at your registrar:

```
tunnel.yourdomain.com   IN NS  address.yourdomain.com
address.yourdomain.com  IN A   SERVER_IP
```


* * *

## CrowdSec

CrowdSec is the bouncer for our DNS port. It watches CoreDNS logs. Any IP that probes the DNS decoy hits 3 queries within 60 seconds triggers a ban enforced by nftables at the kernel level.

```
CoreDNS stdout -> CrowdSec agent -> LAPI -> nftables bouncer -> DROP set
```

### Unban yourself on Crowdsec

If you accidentally trigger a ban during testing:

```bash
sudo cscli decisions delete --ip <your_banned_ip_here>
```


