## Warnings

### Cellular Carriers / Transparent DNS Proxies

What? How could there be any problem with this great idea we've cooked up and spent time on developing this cool script for.

Well, many carriers intercept all UDP port 53 traffic before it leaves their network and attempt to parse it so they can log and correlate it as raw sellable data. 

> A WireGuard handshake is not a DNS query — many carriers drop or corrupt it.


* * *

#### Really? My cell phone provider is modifing traffic

Sure, test it now:

- **Symptom:** Wireguard works on WiFi, fails on cellular.

- **Diagnosis:** `sudo tcpdump -i <iface> -n udp port 53` while connecting from cellular. No packets = carrier blocked it.

- **Fix:** use the iodine DNS tunnel (see post-install menu). iodine encodes traffic as real DNS queries and was designed to survive exactly this.

> What? Iodine is a last resort. Surely, there has got to be a better way.

